		<div>The closest thing that I've had to a world war was the pacts that Greece, Carthage, Babylon, and Persia signed against me in my latest game. I had already conquered Persia and brought it to a single city, a pet civ, and declared war on it every once in a while for fun and money. Babylon was already half-defeated, with its productive cities destroyed. Greece had just begun war with me (see Greece, Thou Hast Done Me Great Wrong) and was quite upset with my apparent ease in taking their cities. Carthage was actually last on my list of civs to conquer, 4 behind Greece.<br />
     As I approached Athens, I saw that the Greeks and the Persians signed an embargo against me. On the same turn, the babylonians officially joined the Greeks. On the next turn, those stupid inferior Carthaginians demanded a tech and declared war on me. Then, they allied with the Greeks against me. The odd thing was, even though the Greeks and Persians had an embargo against me, the Greeks and Babylonians made one against their ally, Persia. I have no idea how they figured that one out.<br />
     Anyway, none of these civs lasted very long until I had reduced them to a single city and surrounded them. Persia was so mad that they declared war on me (they had no units anyway), and waited 10 whole turns before they would even talk to me again! That's my World War.</div>
	</td>
