		<hr />
		
		
			<div><strong>The War Without End</strong><br />&nbsp;</div>
		
		
		
		<div>WARNING -This Is Long. Nearly 6000 characters- WARNING<br />
<br />
<br />
Ok, So I started out on the Dominatrix Map. (I like the isolation):rolleyes: <br />
<br />
I was America on the lower left continent. Clockwise on the other continents staring with the one north of me were the Arabs, then Ottomans, Babylons, Iroquois, Aztecs, Persians, and Zulus.<br />
<br />
Thanks to some AMAZING luck at the beginning of the game mine soon became the largest empire. (Most of the goody huts gave me settlers)<br />
<br />
My empire controlled my entire continent and the left half of the center jungle contintent. I also had one city on the Arab continent and three cities on the Zulu's. The other civies filled their continents and the right half of the jungle continent was a jumble of Ottoman, Zulu, and Persian cities.<br />
<br />
During the game I would only enter Mutual Protection with the Zulu (I dislike tangled webs of alliances, and they asked first. Paid me quite well too!!)<br />
<br />
By the time I reached the modern era my empire was well developed and, well, out of room. So I turned my eyes toward my northern neighbors, the Arabs who were presently mid-Industrial. I quickly built up a force of 8 modern armor (small army, I know but it was SUPPOSED to be a small, quick invasion, not a long, drawn-out conquest)<br />
<br />
I sent this tiny army to the doorstep (how cliché) of the Arab city nearest to my empire. This, of course, did not sit well with them, and they cautiously asked me to move them (they had a larger army, but were the dumbest civy there after the Persians, who were still *snicker* medieval)<br />
<br />
So I say, ok, I'll move them (big, whopping lie) and then demand all their gold, the city I was near, and a world map (on principle) They say no, so I say forget get it.<br />
<br />
The next turn I attack.  Their rifle men were no match for my modern armor, and the city fell with the first unit (which produced my first leader for my first army) I then contact the Ottomans (the Arabs other neighbors) and pay them to join a military alliance.<br />
The Zulus join in by virtue of our Mutual Protection.<br />
<br />
So it me (America), the Ottomans, and the Zulu vs the Arabs.  Then the Babylonians sign a military alliance against me with Arabia (oops) I wasn't too worried because the Babylonians had to travel through Ottoman territory to get to me, so my rear was covered.  Just to be safe though I got Persia to join in on our side, and the Aztecs were forced in because of the Mutual Protection with Persia.<br />
<br />
So after a few turns I had decimated half of Arabia when (CRAP) :eek: the Iroquois signed a military alliance with Babylon against me.  The Iroquois had just entered the modern era and had the largest army. I could not afford to keep up my war with Arabia and fight the Iroquois at the same time.  So I made peace with the Arabs. I got all their gold, three of their cities and their world map (on principle)<br />
<br />
I then shifted my armies (I had 4 now, all filled with modern armor) to the Iroquois Front (the only time I was glad for the absurdity of the railroads free-movement cost) The previous turn a massive Iroquois army had entered and captured a Zulu city on the jungle continent, and could now threaten Zulu, Ottoman, Persian, and more importantly MY cities. So I sent my first army to &quot;liberate&quot; the captured Zulu city (which had few defenders) and the other three armies to destroy as many Iroquois units on the jungle continent as I could. The next turn the Aztecs and the stupid, stupid Persians managed to beat back the Iroquois AND capture two of their cities.<br />
<br />
Thats when everything got out of control. The Ottomans (who had backed out of the war as early as they could) signed a Military Alliance with the Iroquois. So now it was me, the Zulu, the Aztec, and the Persians against the Ottomans, the Babylonians, and the Iroquois. The Arabs were sitting quietly licking their wounds.<br />
<br />
I had my new Invasion force of 6 armies (all modern armor) ready to begin an campaign into the Ottoman continent on my next turn. The Babylonians and Iroquois were both boxed in by the Aztecs who had emerged as a superpower during this long war.<br />
<br />
Then the annoying happened. The Zulu (who still had one city on the jungle continent) bombed Ottomans (who had at some point signed a Mutual Protection with Arabia) So now I am forced to resume my war with Arabia.<br />
<br />
    -side note- even though I still call it the jungle continent, workers had long ago removed all jungles :rolleyes: <br />
<br />
It was then I realized the gargantuan mistake I had made.  I had forgot to put any units in the three cities the Arabs had relinquished to me. I had only one chance.  My armies had to shift and kill the king unit (yes, regicide was on, don't ask stupid questions) for Arabia.<br />
<br />
At this point I noticed that Zulu units were withdrawing. A quick check of the diplomacy screen confirmed it. After dragging me into war with Arabia, Zululand had made peace with everyone and canceled our Mutual Protection. They stabbed me in the back and left me in a lurch.<br />
<br />
My &quot;loyal&quot; puppets :aargh: <br />
<br />
Despite this heinous treachery, I was able to kill Abu (the Arab king unit) and eliminate the Arabs before I lost my three foolishly unprotected cities.<br />
<br />
Now since the start of this war so long ago I had constantly been building modern armor and had quite an impressive occupation army. I was able to force a peace from the Ottomans, Babylonians, and the Iroquois.<br />
<br />
And thus ended my involvement in the war. My part had lasted nearly 300 turns, and the war itself would not end until the destruction of the Iroquois by the Ottomans, Persians, Babylonians, and Zulu 50 turns later (Hiawatha was killed by the evil Zulu)<br />
<br />
When the dust finally settled I had contol over all of my continent, the jungle continent (the final Zulu city converted) and the Arab continent. I also owned the right half of the Iroquios continent, and had gained control of a third of the Zulu continent thru multiple cutural conversions.<br />
<br />
Now about those treacherous Zulu... :evil:</div>
	</td>
</tr>
