		<div>This is from the game I'm currently playing and I'm still in a war with Russia, well this is how it happened.<br />
<br />
I'm playing large map, islands, highest percent of water. I was second to only France, but they were a close ally, but close to the end point I decieded I had to win. So I decided more cities! I scouted the map and found the Germany had 2 cities, and were very low in the tech tree. I signed a few mutual protectin pacts, just in case and went in.<br />
<br />
Note: I have double you pleasure, and was using their mobile infantry units.<br />
<br />
Right before I initiate my 1 turn war on Germany, they pact with the Russians, I go through with it anyway. So I take out Germany then Russia attacks with a ship. It is now<br />
<br />
Japan, America(me), France, Persia vs. Russia. <br />
<br />
I move in to the closet Island, take out all three cities in one swipe, move to the next, take it, then the next. One turn before 2050, I get the UN building and barely beat out France.<br />
<br />
