		<div>This one's ongoing.<br />
<br />
I'm Egypt, playing 5CC at second-easiest difficulty on a small map with four other civs: Rome, Germany and Greece on my continent, and Russia alone on a huge island to the west.<br />
<br />
I'm being meek and mild, keeping everyone else &quot;gracious&quot; with gifts of gold and techs but building up a strong army and keeping a slight tech lead, until the 1600s, when Caesar -- still &quot;gracious,&quot; mind you -- waltzes up to Elephantine with about 2 dozen infantry.<br />
<br />
I signed quick MPPs with everyone else and invited Julius to remove his unwashed hordes from my terrority soonest, which brought a war declaration. :rolleyes: <br />
<br />
So I hit him, hard, with arty. I captured and razed (remember, 5CC) three of his cities. Meanwhile, Germany and Greece settled into trench warfare with Rome (no gains, many casualties), and Russia kept pretty much to herself.<br />
<br />
When that gets old, I get Rome to sign a peace deal and cede me three tiny cities (which I raze), but stupid Otto attacks Greece, which drags me into war with Germany. So that's where I am now, and I've got my sights set on the oil resource next to Koenigsberg.</div>
