		<hr />
		
		
		
		
		<div>My first world war was not suprisingly in my first game. I had just finished conquering Persia, who was on a contient with the Babylonians. I owned the two islansds near my home contient (which I had cleansed of the American and Iroqoius filth- playing Aztecs here) and was mobilizing for a war against Babylon, who was roughly a tech or two behind me the entire game. I just got in industrial and was producing cavalry.<br />
<br />
Nobody liked me because I razed any city they put on land I claimed (my contients and the islands), and we would &quot;war&quot; for about 5 turns, where I would demand peace for a small price on their part. And I always attacked before declaring war. I'm not exactly going for UN here. Anyhoo, the Germans, who are one tech ahead of me thanks to being scentific, demand...printing press? I politely decline, and he declares war on me. A galleon deposits a Knight and a unit of Cavalry, who sweep over my knights and spearmen defending two cities on my smaller isle very quickly. I had several galleons of cavalry en route to Babylonia (Persia had a few cities in their territory, which I was using as a beachead), so I retook my island quickly. I launched an invasion of Germany, razing one city and taking another. Peace was settled, and Frankfurt flipped back. I built my forces up, determining that Germany WOULD die. I was in a MPP with France and England, and  SOMETHING happened over there- a dispute over the ownership of Marseilles. I launched an invasion and cleared the land of the Germans. I had a MASSIVE cavalry force there, so I rushed pikemen in all of my German cities, moved them via French rails to England, and obliterated them with some minor French help. After this, I negotiated ROP with the Babylonians, moved a force of cavalry to each city, declared war, and took several cities in those firt turns. After Babylonia fell, France surrendered to the Dominating Aztec powers. :D</div>
	</td>
</tr>
