		<hr />
		
		
		
		
		<div>I was playing a standard size world map, the kind that comes with the game.<br />
<br />
I was America, and I started out in North America. The Aztecs were in Northern South America / Central America, and the Iroquois were in South America. The Germans were where Russia is in real life. Rome was in Western Europe, Russia was in Africa and Australia, and France was in Asia.<br />
<br />
I had been at war with the Aztecs off and on for most of the game. I had more troops than them, and eventually I gained an advantage and wiped them out. The Iroquois had been my ally early in the game but as the game went on they began to ally themselves with the Aztecs so I wiped them out too.<br />
<br />
Anyway, so then I controlled all of North and South America. For some reason the Germans just didn't like me, and we were at war for possibly 300+ years. They would bomb me every turn, which was really annoying because it slowed down the game, and occasionally try to invade but I held them back. They would never sign a peace treaty, and war weariness in my cities was out of control so I couldn't build anything. I was a Democracy and Germany was a Communism.<br />
<br />
Their country was way too large to invade, and I didn't have enough soldiers and I was unable to build more due to war weariness. Eventually the Germans gave up and decided to make peace. Then they invaded Russia and took over Africa...<br />
<br />
Also the Russians, Romans, and French didn't like me and I was fighting them for most of the game too...<br />
<br />
Anyway, eventually I won the game by winning the Space Race.</div>
